overview: The user's intent was to get a comprehensive review of a sleep
  questionnaire application against its detailed specification and SOW. The
  approach involved a thorough examination of the codebase, including types,
  validations, API routes, and UI components. A detailed plan was then
  generated, outlining both implemented features and identified gaps,
  categorized by priority. Key decisions included prioritizing high-impact
  missing features like a tiredness severity scale, COMISA detection, and
  outbound links. The outcome is the commencement of the implementation phase,
  starting with the integration of a 1-10 tiredness severity scale and
  associated safety messaging, which involved updating types and validation
  schemas.
